{
  "specVersion": "0.4.0",
  "kind": "tsm-scene",
  "id": "upstream-downstream",
  "title": "A minimal ecosystem — two firms linked by a contract",
  "source": "Adapted from Baldwin &amp; Holgersson (2026), <em>Ecosystem evolution: contracts, modules, and standards</em>, Figure 18.1",
  "lenses": ["cyclic-flow", "forward-handoff", "modularity-boundary"],

  "narrative": {
    "mode": "walkthrough",
    "steps": [
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 1 — Two firms, two architectures.</strong> An Upstream job shop and a Downstream flow line, each its own TSM with its own internal architecture. The boundary circles mark each firm. Transfers <em>inside</em> a boundary are paperwork-free; the thin crossing between them is where transactions happen.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": ["diagonal", "overlay:firm-boundary"]
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 2 — Production inside each firm.</strong> Downstream runs a clean flow line: forward hand-offs down the diagonal, kanban pull signals above (the <code>s</code> marks). Upstream is denser — its cell marks fill the matrix, showing that any task there can hand to any other. The contract arrows fade to context.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward",
            "overlay:firm-boundary"
          ]
        },
        "setEmphasis": {
          "primary": { "byLens": ["forward-handoff"], "byMark": ["s"] },
          "secondary": { "byId": ["contract-goods", "contract-payment"] }
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 3 — The contract is the boundary.</strong> Inside each firm, transfers flow without paperwork. Between firms, the contract is the single thin crossing where transactions get recorded. The two contract arrows — goods one way, payment the other — are the headline of this figure; everything else fades.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward",
            "overlay:firm-boundary"
          ]
        },
        "setEmphasis": {
          "primary": { "byId": ["contract-goods", "contract-payment"] },
          "secondary": { "byLens": ["forward-handoff", "cyclic-flow"], "byMark": ["s"] }
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 4 — Together: bilateral exchange under contract.</strong> Internal coordination and the cross-firm contract, both visible. The ecosystem is two firms that could each evolve independently, held in relation by one bilateral agreement. Switch to a single matrix to walk through either firm's internal pattern.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward",
            "overlay:firm-boundary"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  },

  "matrices": [
    {
      "id": "upstream",
      "architectureType": "job-shop",

      "narrative": {
        "mode": "walkthrough",
        "steps": [
          {
            "caption": "<strong>Upstream — Step 1.</strong> Six tasks (U1–U6) line up on the diagonal. The firm boundary draws a circle around the whole matrix; no task sits outside.",
            "reveal": { "include": ["diagonal", "overlay:firm-boundary"] }
          },
          {
            "caption": "<strong>Upstream — Step 2.</strong> Forward transfers fill every cell below the diagonal. Every task can hand work to every later task — this is a classic job-shop pattern. Roles inside the firm are fluid; any actor may pick up any task.",
            "reveal": {
              "include": [
                "diagonal",
                "transfer:directed:forward",
                "overlay:firm-boundary"
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "caption": "<strong>Upstream — Step 3.</strong> Backward transfers fill the rest. The matrix is now fully populated — every off-diagonal cell carries an <code>x</code>. <em>Job-shops are cyclic by design</em>; the validator's flow-dominance check is opted out here.",
            "reveal": {
              "include": [
                "diagonal",
                "transfer:directed:forward",
                "transfer:directed:backward",
                "overlay:firm-boundary"
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "caption": "<strong>Upstream — Step 4.</strong> The boundary circle marks the firm's edge. Everything inside is a transaction-free zone where transfers flow without paperwork. The single arrow leaving the firm (to Downstream) is the contract — that is where transactions live. Switch to <em>Downstream</em> to see what receives.",
            "reveal": {
              "include": [
                "diagonal",
                "transfer:directed:forward",
                "transfer:directed:backward",
                "overlay:firm-boundary"
              ]
            }
          }
        ]
      },

      "regions": [
        { "id": "upstream-firm", "layoutKind": "diagonal-block", "semanticKind": "task", "label": "Upstream (job shop)" }
      ],

      "tasks": [
